      "content": "**Please do not give aspirin to an 8-year-old.** Aspirin can cause a serious condition called Reye's syndrome, which is especially dangerous for children who are sick. Instead, please use acetaminophen (like Tylenol) or ibuprofen (like Advil or Motrin) according to the dosing instructions for his age and weight. If his fever is very high or he seems extremely unwell, please contact your pediatrician right away.",
